With a Rapsberry Pi 3 model b and a 64GB micro SD card, a set-up that is beefier than it needs to be, but who knows what the Pi will be used for in the future&hellip;
#1 Get Raspbian, and format micro SD card&mdash; after much jiggling with the unlock tab on the adapter and delicatelyrepeatedly inserting-half-inserting into 2012 Macbook Pro&rsquo;s gunked-up card reader port&hellip;

In all the years I&rsquo;ve been running OS X (or MacOS as it is now called) I&rsquo;ve never had the need to su,sudo was always good enough. And this is as it should be.
Until now. Obvs, &ldquo;root&rdquo; is disabled in High Sierra. So&hellip;
$ cd /System/Library/CoreServices/Applications/ $ ls Some cool apps here&hellip;
drwxr-xr-x 3 root wheel 96B Mar 30 12:48 About This Mac.app drwxr-xr-x 3 root wheel 96B Mar 30 12:48 Archive Utility.

Having just dropped a couple of 4TB Western Digital NAS drives in the openmediavault box, I can now get around to adding more media. My Moby Dick is split over two DVD disks&hellip; that&rsquo;s a pain. Let&rsquo;s join them&hellip;
The obvious, and lazy, and probably-will-not-work way:
~/MyRips/Moby Dick (1998) $ cat &#34;Moby Dick (1998) - CD 1.avi&#34; &#34;Moby Dick (1998) - CD 2.avi&#34; &gt; &#34;Moby Dick (1998).avi&#34; Video will only play the length of the first file because this is where the avi header information is.

Again with the Openmediavault NAS.
A fair few movies I encoded to result in less than 1080P files in order to preserve disk space. That is not really an issue (for now). So, what movies have what resolution?
(I feel like this should all been in shell script, but hey; whatever works right?!)
[cc lang=&ldquo;ruby&rdquo;] require &lsquo;find&rsquo;
basedir = &lsquo;/Volumes/Movies&rsquo;
get filetypes find . -type f | egrep -i -E -o &ldquo;.

